 <title>How far Have We Come?</title>
 <link>http://www.completelyeco.com/articles/how-far-have-we-come</link>
 <description>
&lt;div class=&quot;serif field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden clearfix&quot;&gt;
  
  &lt;!-- THIS SHOULD BE FOR JUST THE BODY --&gt;
  
  &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Greenspring Energy has been named the 15th fastest growing company in the United States, as recorded by Inc. Magazine. To compile its annual listing, Inc. Magazine assesses companies that are privately held, independent, for profit and based in the U.S. The ranking also accounts for fiscal growth over a three-year period of time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since its opening, Greenspring Energy has achieved a rate of growth of 8,700 percent, demonstrating that public awareness about the positive impact of solar energy, as well as the financial and environmental benefits it carries, is increasing at a rapid pace. The company has evolved steadily since 2007, growing from a team of one at launch to nearly 60 employees today, and branding itself as the premier provider of solar and efficiency products in the Mid-Atlantic region. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“Greenspring Energy is different because we focus on providing customized solutions for our customers that combine both solar and efficiency products,” said Paul Witteman, President and CEO of Greenspring Energy. “Our goal is to work hand-in-hand with our customers to design and install a system that is ideal based on their energy utility patterns and ultimately, what is going to give them the best and quickest return on investment.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operationally, Greenspring Energy has expanded is geographical service area to include much of the central east coast of the U.S., with facilities in Reading, PA and Charlotte, NC, in addition to the company’s headquarter location in Timonium, MD. The company partners with numerous reputable product manufacturers, including Schuco Solar USA, who has presented Greenspring Energy with their “National Residential Dealer of the Year Award” for the past two, consecutive years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;Our selection to the Inc. 500 ranking reflects the widespread acceptance of our unique combination of solar and efficiency products and services,&quot; said Wittemann. &quot;Our customers and dedicated employees have made this achievement possible. We have a lot to be proud of.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moving forward, Greenspring Energy will continue to focus on growth through partnering with new residential and corporate customers, while creating new program to customize and enhance solar solutions for already-existing customers. To schedule an initial consultation, please call 443-322-7000 or visit &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.greenspringenergy.com&quot;&gt;www.greenspringenergy.com&lt;/a&gt; for further information about our complete line of products and services for both residential and commercial buildings.&lt;/p&gt;
